[{"location":"95-reference/#reference","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"95-reference/#Contents","page":"Reference","title":"Contents","text":"Pages = [\"95-reference.md\"]","category":"section"},{"location":"95-reference/#Index","page":"Reference","title":"Index","text":"Pages = [\"95-reference.md\"]","category":"section"},{"location":"95-reference/#TimeFloats.fromfloat-Union{Tuple{S}, Tuple{Type{Dates.Time}, Real, Type{S}}} where S<:Union{Dates.Day, Dates.Hour, Dates.Microsecond, Dates.Millisecond, Dates.Minute, Dates.Nanosecond, Dates.Second, Dates.Week}","page":"Reference","title":"TimeFloats.fromfloat","text":"fromfloat(T<:AbstractTime, x::Real, S<:TimePeriod)\n\nApproximate a float representation of x as a S time persiod to a T. T can be any of the subtypes of TimePeriod (i.e. Nanosecond, Microsecond, Millisecond, Second, Minute, and Hour), Time, and Dates.CompoundPeriod.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> fromfloat(Millisecond, 1, Second)\n1000 milliseconds\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"95-reference/#TimeFloats.fromsecond-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Type{T}, Any}} where T","page":"Reference","title":"TimeFloats.fromsecond","text":"fromsecond(T<:TimePeriod, x)\n\nApproximate a float representation of x in seconds to a T time period. T can be any of the subtypes of TimePeriod (i.e. Nanosecond, Microsecond, Millisecond, Second, Minute, and Hour), Time, or Dates.CompoundPeriod.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> fromsecond(Millisecond, 1.5)\n1500 milliseconds\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"95-reference/#TimeFloats.tofloat-Union{Tuple{S}, Tuple{Type{S}, Dates.Time}} where S<:Union{Dates.Day, Dates.Hour, Dates.Microsecond, Dates.Millisecond, Dates.Minute, Dates.Nanosecond, Dates.Second, Dates.Week}","page":"Reference","title":"TimeFloats.tofloat","text":"tofloat(T<:TimePeriod, x)\n\nConvert x to a float representation of x as a T time period. T can be any of the subtypes of TimePeriod (i.e. Nanosecond, Microsecond, Millisecond, Second, Minute, and Hour). x can be any of the subtypes of TimePeriod, Time, or Dates.CompoundPeriod.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> tofloat(Millisecond, Second(1))\n1000.0\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"95-reference/#TimeFloats.tosecond-Tuple{Any}","page":"Reference","title":"TimeFloats.tosecond","text":"tosecond(x)\n\nConvert x to a float representation of x in seconds. x can be any of the subtypes of TimePeriod (i.e. Nanosecond, Microsecond, Millisecond, Second, Minute, and Hour), Time, or Dates.CompoundPeriod.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> toscond(Millisecond(1500))\n1.5\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#TimeFloats","page":"TimeFloats","title":"TimeFloats","text":"Documentation for TimeFloats.","category":"section"}]
